<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android" android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:gravity="center"
    android:padding="20dp"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    android:background="#292929">

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/abril_fatface"
        android:paddingRight="20dp"
        android:paddingLeft="20dp"
        android:paddingBottom="10dp"
        android:paddingTop="10dp"
        android:text="Instructions:"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="30dp"
        android:textStyle="bold" />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/aladin"
        android:padding="10dp"
        android:text="1. To Add a new task - click on the add menu (plus sign on top side of the app). A dialog will pop up that takes input of your task name, details(not compulsory), date and time. Clicking on the SAVE button you can save the task on your ToDoManger."
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="15dp" />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/aladin"
        android:padding="10dp"
        android:text="2. You can always edit your saved tasks by a long-click on the specific item on the list. You can also mark the task as completed if you complete the task or delete it if you don't plan on doing it."
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="15dp" />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/aladin"
        android:padding="10dp"
        android:text="3. Your tasks are always sorted in order! If finishing times of two or more tasks match up, it is sorted lexicographically."
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="15dp" />

    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/aladin"
        android:padding="10dp"
        android:text="4. You can always view your previously finished tasks in History menu(recycle sign next to add menu). You can remove a specific item from your history by long-click on the specific items or you can clear all at once by selecting 'clear all' menu from top left corner. You can come back any time by clicking on the back arrow next to the menu button."
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="15dp" />
    <TextView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        android:background="@color/white"
        android:fontFamily="@font/aladin"
        android:padding="10dp"
        android:text="5. You will receive notification when it is time for your task. ALso You can click on the notification to open the app to mark or edit it!"
        android:textColor="@color/black"
        android:textSize="15dp" />
    <Button
        android:id="@+id/instructionBackId"
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:layout_gravity="center"
        android:text="Done"
        android:layout_margin="2dp"
        />
</LinearLayout>